Data generation

# Set seed for reproducibility
set.seed(candidate_number)

# Number of observations
n <- 2000

# Generate numeric predictors
rocket_efficiency <- runif(n, min = 0.2, max = 0.9)
payload_weight <- rnorm(n, mean = 500, sd = 150)

# Generate categorical predictors
mission_objective <- factor(sample(c("Planetary Exploration", "Space Telescope Deployment", "Space Station Resupply"), n, replace = TRUE))
launch_vehicle_type <- factor(sample(c("Expendable Launch Vehicle", "Reusable Launch Vehicle"), n, replace = TRUE))

# Data frame version of predictors
space_predictors <- data.frame(
  rocket_efficiency = rocket_efficiency,
  payload_weight = payload_weight,
  mission_objective = mission_objective,
  launch_vehicle_type = launch_vehicle_type
)

# Energy Consumption CEF with nonlinearity and interactions
Energy_Consumption_CEF <- function(rocket_efficiency, payload_weight, mission_objective, launch_vehicle_type) {
  base_energy <- 1000  # Base energy consumption
  
  # Nonlinear adjustment based on rocket efficiency
  energy_adjustment <- -200 * rocket_efficiency^2 + 50 * rocket_efficiency
  
  # Interaction effect between payload weight and mission objective
  payload_mission_adjustment <- ifelse(mission_objective == "Space Station Resupply", 0, -0.2 * payload_weight)
  
  # Interaction effect between launch vehicle type and mission objective
  launch_mission_adjustment <- ifelse(launch_vehicle_type == "Reusable Launch Vehicle" & mission_objective == "Space Telescope Deployment", 150, 0)
  
  # Calculate total energy consumption
  total_energy_consumption <- base_energy + energy_adjustment + payload_mission_adjustment + launch_mission_adjustment
  
  return(total_energy_consumption)
}

# Simulate data with the Energy Consumption CEF
space_data <- space_predictors %>%
  mutate(energy_consumption_Y = Energy_Consumption_CEF(rocket_efficiency, payload_weight, mission_objective, launch_vehicle_type))

#Plotting the residuals of Gam Oracle and Simple


# Predictions and Residuals for gam_oracle

residuals_oracle <- residuals(gam_oracle)

# Predictions and Residuals for gam_simple

residuals_simple <- residuals(gam_simple)

# Create data frames for ggplot

df_simple <- data.frame(Predicted = predictions_simple, Residual = residuals_simple)

#1st concept shift to the CEF



# Set seed for reproducibility
set.seed(candidate_number)

# Number of observations
n <- 2000

# Generate numeric predictors
rocket_efficiency <- runif(n, min = 0.2, max = 0.9)
payload_weight <- rnorm(n, mean = 500, sd = 150)

# Generate categorical predictors
mission_objective <- factor(sample(c("Planetary Exploration", "Space Telescope Deployment", "Space Station Resupply"), n, replace = TRUE))
launch_vehicle_type <- factor(sample(c("Expendable Launch Vehicle", "Reusable Launch Vehicle"), n, replace = TRUE))

# Data frame version of predictors

  rocket_efficiency = rocket_efficiency,
  payload_weight = payload_weight,
  mission_objective = mission_objective,
  launch_vehicle_type = launch_vehicle_type
)

# Energy Consumption CEF with nonlinearity and interactions
Energy_Consumption_CEF <- function(rocket_efficiency, payload_weight, mission_objective, launch_vehicle_type) {
  base_energy <- 1000  # Base energy consumption
  
  # Nonlinear adjustment based on rocket efficiency
  energy_adjustment <- -200 * rocket_efficiency^2 + 50 * rocket_efficiency
  
  # Interaction effect between payload weight and mission objective 
  payload_mission_adjustment <- ifelse(mission_objective == "Space Station Resupply", 0, 0.2 * payload_weight)
  
  # Interaction effect between launch vehicle type and mission objective
  launch_mission_adjustment <- ifelse(launch_vehicle_type == "Reusable Launch Vehicle" & mission_objective == "Space Telescope Deployment", 150, 0)
  
  # Calculate total energy consumption (Changed)
  total_energy_consumption <- 1.5*base_energy + energy_adjustment + payload_mission_adjustment + launch_mission_adjustment
  
  return(total_energy_consumption)
}

  launch_vehicle_type = launch_vehicle_type

# Energy Consumption CEF with nonlinearity and interactions
Energy_Consumption_CEF <- function(rocket_efficiency, payload_weight, mission_objective, launch_vehicle_type) {
  base_energy <- 1000  # Base energy consumption
  
  # Nonlinear adjustment based on rocket efficiency
  energy_adjustment <- -200 * rocket_efficiency^2 + 50 * rocket_efficiency
  
  # Interaction effect between payload weight and mission objective
  payload_mission_adjustment <- ifelse(mission_objective == "Space Station Resupply", 0, -0.2 * payload_weight)
  
  # Interaction effect between launch vehicle type and mission objective 
  launch_mission_adjustment <- ifelse(launch_vehicle_type == "Reusable Launch Vehicle" & mission_objective == "Space Telescope Deployment", 150, 0)
  
  # Calculate total energy consumption (Changed)
  total_energy <- base_energy + energy_adjustment + (payload_mission_adjustment)^2 + launch_mission_adjustment 
  
  return(total_energy)
}

Covariate shift

[15 marks] 5 for each shift satisfying the desired conditions (one better, one worse), and 5 for the overall quality of the examples, output, and explanation

  • In this section, the conditional distribution of the outcome should stay the same, but the (joint) distribution of the predictor variables should be different

  base_energy <- 1000  # Base energy consumption

  energy_adjustment <- -200 * rocket_efficiency^2 + 50 * rocket_efficiency
